## Functional Requirements

### FR 1: Stock Transfer Screen & Basic Setup

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-100** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to start a stock transfer directly from the Items List screen, so that I can quickly move inventory between locations. | **1. Accessing the Stock Transfer Screen**<br>• **Given** I am in the "Items List" screen<br>• **When** I click "New Stock Transfer" button next to the "Manage Locations" button<br>• **Then** I am taken to the New/Edit Stock Transfer screen<br><br>**2. Stock Transfer Screen Layout**<br>• **Given** I am on the New/Edit Stock Transfer Screen<br>• **Then** I see the following: Stock Transfer # (Required input field), Created Date (defaults to date of creation but can be manually updated), Reason (optional text field), Source Location (Dropdown required field allowing users to select 1 source location from all active locations), Destination Location (Dropdown required field allowing users to select 1 destination location from all active locations), An table below the above fields that has columns: Items, Transfer Quantity, Available Quantity at Source Location, Available Quantity at Destination Location<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field is not visible<br>• **And** the Received Date field is not visible<br><br>**3. Stock Transfer # is required**<br>• **Given** I am on a new stock transfer screen<br>• **When** I attempt to save the stock transfer without entering a Stock Transfer #<br>• **Then** an inline validation message appears "Stock Transfer # is required."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the Stock Transfer # field is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**4. Stock Transfer # must be unique**<br>• **Given** I am creating or editing a stock transfer<br>• **When** I enter a Stock Transfer # that already exists in the system<br>• **And** I attempt to save<br>• **Then** an inline validation message appears "This Stock Transfer # already exists. Please enter a unique number."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the Stock Transfer # field is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**5. Clearing Stock Transfer # validation errors**<br>• **Given** the Stock Transfer # field was previously invalid<br>• **When** I enter a valid, unique Stock Transfer #<br>• **Then** any inline validation messages related to Stock Transfer # are removed<br>• **And** the field returns to its normal, non-error state<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved (assuming all other required fields are valid) | None |
| **FR-101** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to select exactly one Source Location and one Destination Location from my active locations when creating a stock transfer, so that I can accurately define where inventory is moving from and to. | **1. Source and Destination Dropdown Behaviour**<br>• **Given** my account has one or more active locations<br>• **When** I open the Source/Destination Location dropdown<br>• **Then** I see a list of all active locations for the account allowing me to only choose 1 per dropdown<br>• **And** when I attempt to save the stock transfer without selecting a Source/Destination Location<br>• **Then** an inline validation message is shown "Source Location is required", and/or "Destination Location is required"<br><br>**2. Source and Destination Locations cannot be the same**<br>• **Given** I have selected a Source/Destination Location that are the same<br>• **Then** an inline validation message is shown: "Source and Destination cannot be the same location."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer until the conflict is resolved<br>• **And** the invalid field (Destination or Source, depending on which was last selected) is visually highlighted following standard error UI patterns | None |

### FR 2: Item Selection & Quantity Validation

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-200** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to choose an item from a filtered list that only shows items with stock available at the Source Location, so that I can ensure I am transferring valid inventory. | **1. Item dropdown shows only active Inventory Part items linked to the Source Location**<br>• **Given** a Source/Destination Location have been selected<br>• **When** I open the Item dropdown in the table<br>• **Then** I see only active Inventory Part items that meet all of the following criteria: The item is linked to the Source Location, The item has Available Qty > 0 at the Source Location<br>• **And** if no source/destination location have been selected<br>• **Then** the dropdown is empty<br><br>**2. Selecting an item auto-populates availability fields**<br>• **Given** I have selected an Item from the dropdown<br>• **Then** the Available Qty at Source/Destination Location fields auto-populate using the item's current availability at each Location (Quantity in Stock in Location - Committed stock in Location + Expected Stock in Location)<br>• **And** if selected item is not linked at all to the destination location in any transaction then it shows 0<br>• **And** both fields are read-only<br><br>**3. Duplicate items allowed in transfer**<br>• **Given** I am adding line items to a stock transfer<br>• **When** I add an item that already exists in another line item<br>• **Then** the system allows the duplicate item to be added as a separate line item<br>• **And** both line items are treated independently for quantity tracking<br>• **And** each line item's transfer quantity impacts inventory separately | FR-101 |
| **FR-201** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, after selecting an item for a stock transfer, I want to only enter a transfer quantity that is greater than zero and does not exceed the available quantity at the Source Location, so that inventory cannot be over-transferred or recorded incorrectly. | **1. Transfer Qty must be a number greater than 0**<br>• **Given** I am entering a value in the Transfer Qty field<br>• **When** I enter a value that is 0, negative, or non-numeric<br>• **Then** an inline validation message appears "Transfer quantity must be greater than 0."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the row is highlighted according to standard error UI patterns<br><br>**2. Transfer Qty cannot exceed Available Qty at Source Location**<br>• **Given** I have selected an item<br>• **And** the system has auto-populated Available Qty at Source Location<br>• **When** I enter a Transfer Qty that is greater than the available quantity at the source<br>• **Then** a show message appears saying "Transfer quantity cannot exceed available quantity at source."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the Transfer Qty field is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**3. Entering a valid Transfer Qty clears validation errors**<br>• **Given** the Transfer Qty field was previously invalid<br>• **When** I update the value to a number greater than 0 and less than or equal to the available quantity at the source<br>• **Then** any inline validation messages related to Transfer Qty are removed<br>• **And** the field returns to its normal, non-error state<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved (assuming all other required fields are valid) | FR-200 |
| **FR-116** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, when I create or edit a stock transfer, I want to be prevented from saving a transfer without any line items, so that only valid transfers with actual inventory movements are recorded. | **1. Prevent saving transfer with no line items**<br>• **Given** I am creating or editing a stock transfer<br>• **And** I have not added any line items to the transfer<br>• **When** I attempt to click "Save", "In Transit", or "Received"<br>• **Then** a validation message appears "At least one line item is required."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the items table area is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**2. Prevent saving after removing all line items**<br>• **Given** I am editing an existing stock transfer with line items<br>• **And** I remove all line items from the transfer<br>• **When** I attempt to save the stock transfer<br>• **Then** a validation message appears "At least one line item is required."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the items table area is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**3. Clearing validation after adding line item**<br>• **Given** I attempted to save a stock transfer with no line items<br>• **And** a validation error is displayed<br>• **When** I add at least one line item with valid item, transfer quantity, and locations<br>• **Then** the validation message is removed<br>• **And** the items table area returns to its normal, non-error state<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved (assuming all other required fields are valid) | None |

### Status Management (Save, In Transit, Received)

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-104** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to save a stock transfer as "Open" without updating dispatch or received dates, so that I can create draft transfers to complete later. | **1. Save button creates transfer in Open status**<br>• **Given** I am on a new unsaved stock transfer screen<br>• **And** all required fields are valid<br>• **When** I click the "Save" button<br>• **Then** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the user sees a success show message "Stock transfer saved successfully"<br>• **And** the transfer remains on the edit screen for further modifications if desired<br><br>**2. Dispatched and Received date fields remain hidden**<br>• **Given** I am saving a stock transfer using the "Save" button<br>• **When** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "Open"<br>• **Then** the Dispatched Date field remains hidden<br>• **And** the Received Date field remains hidden<br>• **And** only the Created Date is populated<br><br>**3. Transfer can be edited after saving**<br>• **Given** I have saved a stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I navigate back to the stock transfer record<br>• **Then** I can edit all fields including Source Location, Destination Location, items, and quantities<br>• **And** I can click "Save" again to update the transfer<br>• **And** I can click "In Transit" or "Received" to progress the transfer status if desired<br><br>**4. Unsaved changes are not persisted**<br>• **Given** I am creating or editing a stock transfer<br>• **And** I have made changes to fields or line items<br>• **When** I leave the screen, refresh the page, close the browser window, or navigate away without clicking "Save", "In Transit", or "Received"<br>• **Then** all unsaved changes are discarded<br>• **And** the stock transfer reverts to its last saved state<br>• **And** no inventory quantities are affected | FR-100, FR-101, FR-102, FR-103, FR-116 |
| **FR-105** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to mark a stock transfer as "In Transit" with a dispatched date, so that I can track when inventory has left the source location. | **1. In Transit button shows Dispatched Date field and sets status**<br>• **Given** I am on a new unsaved stock transfer screen<br>• **And** all required fields are valid<br>• **When** I click the "In Transit" button<br>• **Then** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field appears<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date is automatically populated with today's date but can be changed if desired<br>• **And** the user sees a success message "Stock transfer marked as in transit"<br><br>**2. Received date field remains hidden**<br>• **Given** I am saving a stock transfer using the "In Transit" button<br>• **When** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **Then** the Received Date field remains hidden<br>• **And** the Received Date field only appears when the transfer status is changed to "Received"<br><br>**3. Editing an In Transit transfer**<br>• **Given** I have saved a stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **When** I navigate back to the stock transfer record<br>• **Then** the only fields that are non-editable are source/destination dropdowns<br>• **And** the items table (Items, Transfer Quantity) is locked and cannot be modified<br><br>**4. Transitioning from Open to In Transit**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I open the transfer and click the "In Transit" button<br>• **Then** the Status changes to "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field appears populated with today's date (but can be edited)<br>• **And** the Received Date field remains hidden<br>• **And** all other transfer details remain unchanged | FR-100, FR-101, FR-102, FR-103, FR-116 |
| **FR-106** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to mark a stock transfer as "Received" with both dispatched and received dates, so that I can record when inventory has arrived at the destination location. | **1. Received button shows both date fields and sets status**<br>• **Given** I am on a new unsaved stock transfer screen<br>• **And** all required fields are valid<br>• **When** I click the "Received" button<br>• **Then** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "Received"<br>• **And** the Dispatched and Received Date fields appears automatically populated with today's date (can be edited)<br>• **And** the user sees a success message "Stock transfer marked as received"<br><br>**2. Transfer is finalized when received**<br>• **Given** I am saving a stock transfer using the "Received" button<br>• **When** the stock transfer is saved with Status = "Received"<br>• **Then** the transfer record is locked from further editing of core fields (Source Location, Destination Location, items, quantities)<br><br>**3. Transitioning from In Transit to Received**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field is visible and already populated<br>• **When** I open the transfer and click the "Received" button<br>• **Then** the Status changes to "Received"<br>• **And** the Received Date field appears is populated with today's date (but can be edited)<br>• **And** the existing Dispatched Date remains unchanged and visible<br><br>**4. Transitioning from Open to Received**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I open the transfer and click the "Received" button<br>• **Then** the Status changes to "Received"<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field appears is populated with today's date (but can be edited)<br>• **And** the Received Date field appears populated with today's date (but can be edited)<br><br>**5. Dispatched Date must be less than or equal to Received Date**<br>• **Given** I am editing a stock transfer with Status = "Received" or "In Transit"<br>• **And** both Dispatched Date and Received Date fields are visible<br>• **When** I enter a Dispatched Date that is greater than the Received Date<br>• **Then** an inline validation message appears "Dispatched date must be on or before received date."<br>• **And** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field is visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**6. Clearing date validation errors**<br>• **Given** the Dispatched Date field was previously invalid due to being after Received Date<br>• **When** I update the Dispatched Date to be on or before the Received Date<br>• **Then** any inline validation messages related to date validation are removed<br>• **And** the field returns to its normal, non-error state<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved (assuming all other required fields are valid) | FR-107 |

### Inventory Impact - Open Status

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-107** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I save a stock transfer as "Open", I want inventory quantities to be reserved at the source and expected at the destination, so that my available inventory reflects pending transfers. | **1. Saving Open transfer commits quantity at source location**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "Save" to save the transfer as Status = "Open"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the source location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**2. Saving Open transfer adds expected quantity at destination location**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "Save" to save the transfer as Status = "Open"<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**3. Available quantities recalculate at both locations**<br>• **Given** I have saved a stock transfer as Status = "Open"<br>• **When** the transfer is saved<br>• **Then** the Available quantity at Source and destination Location = Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** both locations reflect the updated Available quantities immediately<br><br>**4. Multiple line items each impact quantities independently**<br>• **Given** I am creating a stock transfer with multiple line items<br>• **When** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** each line item's transfer quantity is added to Committed at the source location for that specific item<br>• **And** each line item's transfer quantity is added to Expected at the destination location for that specific item<br>• **And** Available quantities recalculate independently for each item at both locations | None |
| **FR-108** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I change the transfer quantity on an Open stock transfer, I want inventory reservations to update accordingly, so that my available inventory remains accurate. | **1. Increasing transfer quantity updates committed and expected**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a specific transfer quantity<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and increase the transfer quantity<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the source location increases by the difference<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location increases by the difference<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations<br><br>**2. Decreasing transfer quantity updates committed and expected**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a specific transfer quantity<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and decrease the transfer quantity<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the source location decreases by the difference<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location decreases by the difference<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations | FR-107 |
| **FR-109** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I change items or locations on an Open stock transfer, I want the inventory impact to move to the new item/location, so that reservations stay accurate. | **1. Changing item releases old item and commits new item**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a transfer quantity at a source location<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and change the item to a different item<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the original item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity for the new item at the source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the original item at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the new item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantities recalculate for both items at both locations<br><br>**2. Changing source location moves committed quantity**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a transfer quantity at a specific source location<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and change the source location to a different location<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the original source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity for the item at the new source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both the original and new source locations for the item<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location remains unchanged<br><br>**3. Changing destination location moves expected quantity**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a transfer quantity at a specific destination location<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and change the destination location to a different location<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the original destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the item at the new destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both the original and new destination locations for the item<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location remains unchanged<br><br>**4. Changing both item and source location**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a transfer quantity at a source location<br>• **When** I edit the transfer and change both the item and the source location<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the original item at the original source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity for the new item at the new source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the original item at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the new item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantities recalculate for all affected item/location combinations<br><br>**5. Changing item, quantity, and locations simultaneously**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has an item with a transfer quantity at specific source and destination locations<br>• **When** I edit the transfer changing the item, transfer quantity, source location, and destination location<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the original item at the original source location decreases by the original transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity for the new item at the new source location increases by the new transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the original item at the original destination location decreases by the original transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity for the new item at the new destination location increases by the new transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantities recalculate for all affected combinations | FR-107 |
| **FR-117** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I delete a line item from an Open stock transfer and save, I want the inventory reservations for that item to be released at both locations, so that my available inventory accurately reflects current pending transfers. | **1. Deleting line item releases committed quantity at source**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has a line item with Committed quantity at the source location<br>• **When** I delete the line item from the transfer<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the source location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the source location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**2. Deleting line item releases expected quantity at destination**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has a line item with Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I delete the line item from the transfer<br>• **And** I click "Save"<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the destination location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**3. Both locations update atomically when deleting line item**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I delete a line item and click "Save"<br>• **Then** the source location updates (Committed decreases)<br>• **And** the destination location updates (Expected decreases)<br>• **And** both locations' Available quantities recalculate<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction<br><br>**4. Deleting multiple line items releases quantities independently**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open" with multiple line items<br>• **When** I delete multiple line items and click "Save"<br>• **Then** each deleted line item's transfer quantity is released from Committed at the source location for that specific item<br>• **And** each deleted line item's transfer quantity is released from Expected at the destination location for that specific item<br>• **And** Available quantities recalculate independently for each affected item at both locations<br><br>**5. Deleting duplicate item line item only releases that line's quantity**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the same item appears in multiple line items<br>• **When** I delete one line item for that item and click "Save"<br>• **Then** only that specific line item's transfer quantity is released from Committed at the source<br>• **And** only that specific line item's transfer quantity is released from Expected at the destination<br>• **And** the remaining line items for the same item are unaffected | FR-107 |

### Inventory Impact - Creating New Transfers

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-113** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I create a new stock transfer and mark it directly as "In Transit", I want inventory to physically leave the source location, so that my system accurately reflects that inventory has been dispatched. | **1. Creating new transfer as In Transit decreases quantity on hand at source location**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "In Transit" to save the transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**2. Creating new transfer as In Transit adds expected quantity at destination location**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "In Transit" to save the transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**3. Both locations update atomically when creating as In Transit**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer<br>• **When** I click "In Transit"<br>• **Then** the source location updates (Quantity on Hand decreases)<br>• **And** the destination location updates (Expected quantity increases)<br>• **And** both locations' Available quantities recalculate<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction | FR-100, FR-101, FR-102, FR-103, FR-116 |
| **FR-114** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I create a new stock transfer and mark it directly as "Received", I want inventory quantities to immediately update at both locations, so that physical stock movements are accurately reflected. | **1. Creating new transfer as Received decreases quantity on hand at source**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "Received" to save the transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location remains at zero (never increased)<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**2. Creating new transfer as Received increases quantity on hand at destination**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer and entered all required information<br>• **When** I click "Received" to save the transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location remains at zero (never increased)<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br><br>**3. Both locations update atomically when creating as received**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer<br>• **When** I click "Received"<br>• **Then** the source location updates (Quantity on Hand decreases)<br>• **And** the destination location updates (Quantity on Hand increases)<br>• **And** both locations' Available quantities recalculate<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction<br><br>**4. Committed and Expected quantities are never created**<br>• **Given** I am creating a new stock transfer<br>• **When** I click "Received" to save the transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity at the source location is never increased (remains unchanged)<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location is never increased (remains unchanged)<br>• **And** only Quantity on Hand changes at both locations | FR-100, FR-101, FR-102, FR-103, FR-116 |

### Inventory Impact - Existing Transfers

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-110** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I change a stock transfer from "Open" to "In Transit", I want inventory to physically leave the source location, so that my system accurately reflects that inventory has been dispatched and is no longer at the source. | **1. Changing Open to In Transit decreases quantity on hand at source**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has Committed quantity at the source location<br>• **When** I click "In Transit" to change the status<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity at the source location decreases to zero<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the source location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**2. Changing Open to In Transit maintains expected quantity at destination**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I click "In Transit" to change the status<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the destination location remains unchanged<br><br>**3. Both locations update atomically when transitioning to In Transit**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I click "In Transit"<br>• **Then** the source location updates (Committed decreases to zero, Quantity on Hand decreases)<br>• **And** the destination location maintains Expected quantity<br>• **And** both locations' Available quantities recalculate<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction | FR-107 |
| **FR-111** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I change a stock transfer from "Open" directly to "Received", I want inventory quantities to update at both locations, so that physical stock is accurately reflected at the source and destination. | **1. Changing Open to Received releases committed quantity at source**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has Committed quantity at the source location<br>• **When** I click "Received" to change the status directly from Open to Received<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the source location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**2. Changing Open to Received releases expected quantity and increases stock at destination**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I click "Received" to change the status directly from Open to Received<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the destination location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**3. Both locations update atomically when receiving**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I click "Received"<br>• **Then** the source location updates (Committed decreases, Quantity on Hand decreases)<br>• **And** the destination location updates (Expected decreases, Quantity on Hand increases)<br>• **And** both locations' Available quantities recalculate<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction | FR-107 |
| **FR-112** | DRAFT | Backend | As a user, when I change a stock transfer from "In Transit" to "Received", I want inventory quantities to update at the destination location, so that physical stock is accurately reflected when inventory arrives. | **1. Changing In Transit to Received has no impact on source location**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location has already decreased when the transfer was marked In Transit<br>• **When** I click "Received" to change the status from In Transit to Received<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand at the source location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location remains at zero<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the source location remains unchanged<br><br>**2. Changing In Transit to Received releases expected quantity and increases stock at destination**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I click "Received" to change the status from In Transit to Received<br>• **Then** the Expected quantity for the item at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand for the item at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity at the destination location recalculates as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br><br>**3. Destination location updates atomically when receiving**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **When** I click "Received"<br>• **Then** the destination location updates (Expected decreases, Quantity on Hand increases)<br>• **And** the destination Available quantity recalculates<br>• **And** all updates succeed or fail as a single atomic transaction | FR-107 |

### Stock Transfers List View

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-118** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to view a list of all stock transfers from the Items List screen, so that I can track, filter, and manage all inventory movements between locations. | **1. Accessing Stock Transfers List**<br>• **Given** I am on the Items List screen<br>• **When** I click the "Stock Transfers" tab next to the "Adjusted Stock" tab<br>• **Then** I am taken to the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **And** I see a table displaying all stock transfers<br><br>**2. Stock Transfers List table displays transfer details**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **And** stock transfers exist in the system<br>• **When** the list loads<br>• **Then** I see a table with the following columns: Stock Transfer #, Created Date, Source Location, Destination Location, Reason, Status<br>• **And** each row represents one stock transfer<br>• **And** the table displays all stock transfers sorted by Created Date (most recent first)<br><br>**3. Empty state when no transfers exist**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **And** no stock transfers have been created in the system<br>• **When** the list loads<br>• **Then** I see an empty state message "No stock transfers found"<br>• **And** the table columns are still visible<br>• **And** I can still access the "New Stock Transfer" button to create a transfer<br><br>**4. Search for stock transfers**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **When** I enter text in the search field<br>• **Then** the table displays only stock transfers matching the search criteria<br>• **And** clearing the search field shows all transfers<br><br>**5. Filter by Status**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **When** I select a status from the Status filter dropdown<br>• **Then** the table displays only stock transfers with the selected status<br>• **And** the available status options are: All Statuses (default), Open, In Transit, Received<br>• **And** selecting "All Statuses" removes the filter and shows all transfers<br><br>**6. Filter by Date Range, Source Location, and Destination Location**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **When** I select filter criteria from Date Range, Source Location, or Destination Location filters<br>• **Then** the table displays only stock transfers matching the selected criteria<br>• **And** Date Range filter uses Created Date with inclusive start and end dates<br>• **And** Source Location and Destination Location filters show all active locations<br>• **And** clearing any filter removes that filter and shows all matching transfers<br><br>**7. Clicking a row opens the transfer for editing**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **And** I see one or more stock transfers in the table<br>• **When** I click on any row in the table<br>• **Then** I am taken to the New/Edit Stock Transfer screen for that specific transfer<br>• **And** all fields are populated with the transfer's current data<br>• **And** I can edit the transfer according to the rules defined in FR-104, FR-105, and FR-106<br><br>**8. List updates reflect all changes to transfers**<br>• **Given** I have made changes to a stock transfer<br>• **When** I return to the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **Then** the table reflects all updated information including: Updated Source Location, Updated Destination Location, Updated Status, Updated Dates, Updated Reason<br>• **And** newly created stock transfers appear in the list immediately<br>• **And** the list remains sorted by Created Date (most recent first)<br><br>**9. Multiple filters and search can be applied simultaneously**<br>• **Given** I am on the Stock Transfers List view<br>• **When** I apply search text and multiple filters simultaneously<br>• **Then** the table displays only stock transfers that match all selected criteria<br>• **And** the search and filters work together using AND logic | FR-100 through FR-117 |

### Validation & Error Handling

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-115** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, when I reopen an existing Open stock transfer, I want to be alerted if the available quantity at the source location has dropped below the transfer quantity, so that I can adjust the transfer or take corrective action before proceeding. | **1. Insufficient quantity banner warning when reopening Open transfer**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the available quantity at the source location has dropped below the transfer quantity since the transfer was last saved<br>• **When** I open the stock transfer for editing<br>• **Then** a warning banner appears at the top of the transfer screen<br>• **And** the banner message states "Available quantity at source has changed. One or more line items have insufficient quantity. Review and adjust transfer quantities before saving."<br>• **And** the affected line items' Transfer Qty fields are visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**2. Validation prevents saving with insufficient quantity**<br>• **Given** I have reopened an Open stock transfer with insufficient available quantity at the source<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I attempt to save the stock transfer without adjusting the transfer quantities<br>• **Then** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the banner and field highlights remain visible<br>• **And** an inline validation message appears on each affected Transfer Qty field "Transfer quantity exceeds available quantity at source."<br><br>**3. Clearing insufficient quantity validation**<br>• **Given** I have reopened an Open stock transfer with insufficient available quantity<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I reduce all affected transfer quantities to be less than or equal to the current available quantity at the source<br>• **Then** the warning banner is removed<br>• **And** the Transfer Qty field highlights are removed<br>• **And** the inline validation messages are removed<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved<br><br>**4. Multiple line items with insufficient quantity**<br>• **Given** I have reopened an Open stock transfer with multiple line items<br>• **And** more than one line item has insufficient available quantity at the source<br>• **When** the transfer is opened<br>• **Then** the warning banner appears at the top<br>• **And** all affected line items' Transfer Qty fields are highlighted with errors<br>• **And** the system prevents saving until all quantity issues are resolved<br><br>**5. Banner provides actionable guidance**<br>• **Given** I see the insufficient quantity banner<br>• **Then** the banner message clearly explains the issue and recommends reducing transfer quantities<br>• **And** the affected line items are visually identifiable | None |
| **FR-119** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, when I open an existing stock transfer with an inactive source or destination location, I want to be alerted with actionable guidance, so that I can resolve the issue before proceeding with the transfer. | **1. Inactive location banner warning when opening transfer**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** either the source location or destination location has been made inactive since the transfer was created<br>• **When** I open the stock transfer for editing<br>• **Then** a warning banner appears at the top of the transfer screen and states "This order references inactive locations. Please reassign to an active location or reactivate the inactive location to proceed with this transfer."<br><br>**2. System prevents saving until location is resolved**<br>• **Given** I have opened a stock transfer with an inactive source or destination location<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I attempt to save, mark as "In Transit", or mark as "Received"<br>• **Then** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the warning banner remains visible<br>• **And** an inline validation message appears "Cannot save transfer with inactive location."<br><br>**3. Banner clears when location is made active or changed**<br>• **Given** I have opened a stock transfer with an inactive location<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I change the inactive location to an active location<br>• **Then** the warning banner is removed<br>• **And** the location field highlight is removed<br>• **And** the inline validation messages are removed<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved | FR-101 |
| **FR-120** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, when I open an existing stock transfer with one or more inactive items, I want to be alerted with actionable guidance, so that I can resolve the issue before proceeding with the transfer. | **1. Inactive item banner warning when opening transfer**<br>• **Given** I have an existing stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** one or more items in the transfer have been made inactive since the transfer was created<br>• **When** I open the stock transfer for editing<br>• **Then** a warning banner appears at the top of the transfer screen and states "This order references inactive items. Please remove inactive items or reactivate them to proceed with this transfer."<br>• **And** the affected line items are visually highlighted using standard error patterns<br><br>**2. System prevents saving until items are resolved**<br>• **Given** I have opened a stock transfer with one or more inactive items<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I attempt to save, mark as "In Transit", or mark as "Received"<br>• **Then** the system prevents saving the stock transfer<br>• **And** the warning banner remains visible<br>• **And** an inline validation message appears "Cannot save transfer with inactive items."<br><br>**3. Banner clears when items are made active or removed**<br>• **Given** I have opened a stock transfer with inactive items<br>• **And** the warning banner is displayed<br>• **When** I either remove all inactive items from the transfer or reactivate all inactive items<br>• **Then** the warning banner is removed<br>• **And** the line item highlights are removed<br>• **And** the inline validation messages are removed<br>• **And** the stock transfer can be saved<br>• **And** the committed, expected, and available quantities update appropriately. | FR-102, FR-117 |

### Permissions, Deletion, & Reverting

| FR ID | Status | Design/Backend | User Story | Acceptance Criteria | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|----------------|------------|---------------------|--------------|
| **FR-121** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want stock transfer functionality to respect my Items app permissions, so that only users with appropriate access can create and manage stock transfers. | **1. New Stock Transfer button visibility based on permissions**<br>• **Given** I am viewing the Items List screen<br>• **When** I have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **Then** I see the "New Stock Transfer" button<br>• **And** clicking the button takes me to the New/Edit Stock Transfer screen<br>• **When** I do not have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **Then** the "New Stock Transfer" button is hidden<br><br>**2. Stock Transfers tab visibility based on permissions**<br>• **Given** I am viewing the Items List screen<br>• **When** I have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **Then** I see the "Stock Transfers" tab<br>• **When** I do not have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **Then** the "Stock Transfers" tab is hidden<br><br>**3. Edit and delete permissions**<br>• **Given** I have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **When** I open a stock transfer<br>• **Then** I can edit and delete the stock transfer<br>• **Given** I do not have "Manage" permissions for the Items app<br>• **Then** I cannot access, edit, or delete any stock transfers | FR-100, FR-118 |
| **FR-122** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to delete stock transfers and reverse their inventory impact, so that I can remove transfers that are no longer needed and restore accurate inventory levels. | **1. Delete button availability by status**<br>• **Given** I am viewing or editing a stock transfer<br>• **When** the transfer has Status = "Open", "In Transit", or "Received"<br>• **Then** I see a "Delete" button on the stock transfer screen<br>• **And** the Delete button is enabled for all three statuses<br><br>**2. Confirmation message for Open transfer deletion**<br>• **Given** I am viewing a stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **When** I click the "Delete" button<br>• **Then** a confirmation dialog appears with the message: "Deleting this transfer will reverse all committed and expected transfer quantities at source and destination locations. This action cannot be undone. Are you sure you want to proceed?"<br>• **And** the dialog includes "Cancel" and "Delete" buttons<br>• **When** I click "Cancel"<br>• **Then** the dialog closes and the transfer is not deleted<br>• **When** I click "Delete"<br>• **Then** the transfer is deleted and inventory is reversed<br><br>**3. Confirmation message for In Transit transfer deletion**<br>• **Given** I am viewing a stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **When** I click the "Delete" button<br>• **Then** a confirmation dialog appears with the message: "Deleting this transfer will reverse all inventory changes at source and destination locations. This action cannot be undone. Are you sure you want to proceed?"<br>• **And** the dialog includes "Cancel" and "Delete" buttons<br>• **When** I click "Cancel"<br>• **Then** the dialog closes and the transfer is not deleted<br>• **When** I click "Delete"<br>• **Then** the transfer is deleted and inventory is reversed<br><br>**4. Confirmation message for Received transfer deletion**<br>• **Given** I am viewing a stock transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **When** I click the "Delete" button<br>• **Then** a confirmation dialog appears with the message: "Deleting this transfer will reverse all inventory changes at source and destination locations. This action cannot be undone. Are you sure you want to proceed?"<br>• **And** the dialog includes "Cancel" and "Delete" buttons<br>• **When** I click "Cancel"<br>• **Then** the dialog closes and the transfer is not deleted<br>• **When** I click "Delete"<br>• **Then** the transfer is deleted and inventory is reversed<br><br>**5. Deleting Open transfer reverses inventory reservations**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with Status = "Open"<br>• **And** the transfer has Committed quantity at the source location<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I confirm deletion of the transfer<br>• **Then** the Committed quantity at the source location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at both locations remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** the stock transfer record is permanently deleted from the system<br>• **And** I see a success message "Stock transfer deleted successfully"<br>• **And** I am redirected to the Stock Transfers List view<br><br>**6. Deleting In Transit transfer reverses inventory changes**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location has already decreased<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I confirm deletion of the transfer<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand at the source location increases by the transfer quantity (reversing the decrease)<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location remains at zero (was never created)<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** the stock transfer record is permanently deleted from the system<br>• **And** I see a success message "Stock transfer deleted successfully"<br>• **And** I am redirected to the Stock Transfers List view<br><br>**7. Deleting Received transfer reverses completed transfer**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location has decreased<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the destination location has increased<br>• **When** I confirm deletion of the transfer<br>• **Then** the Quantity on Hand at the source location increases by the transfer quantity (reversing the decrease)<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity (reversing the increase)<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location remains at zero (was never created)<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location remains at zero (was never created)<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** the stock transfer record is permanently deleted from the system<br>• **And** I see a success message "Stock transfer deleted successfully"<br>• **And** I am redirected to the Stock Transfers List view<br><br>**8. All deletions are atomic transactions**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with multiple line items<br>• **And** the transfer can have Status = "Open", "In Transit", or "Received"<br>• **When** I confirm deletion of the transfer<br>• **Then** each line item's inventory impact is reversed independently<br>• **And** all line items for the same item have their quantities summed and reversed<br>• **And** all inventory updates complete atomically | FR-107, FR-110, FR-111, FR-112, FR-117, FR-118 |
| **FR-123** | DRAFT | Both | As a user, I want to revert In Transit and Received transfers back to Open status, so that I can update transfer details and inventory is accurately reversed. | **1. Revert button availability for In Transit and Received statuses**<br>• **Given** I am viewing or editing a stock transfer<br>• **When** the transfer has Status = "In Transit" or Status = "Received"<br>• **Then** I see a "Revert to Open" button on the stock transfer screen<br>• **And** the button is enabled for both In Transit and Received statuses<br>• **When** the transfer has Status = "Open"<br>• **Then** the "Revert to Open" button is not visible<br><br>**2. Confirmation message for In Transit revert**<br>• **Given** I am viewing a stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **When** I click the "Revert to Open" button<br>• **Then** a confirmation dialog appears with the message: "Reverting this transfer to Open will reverse all inventory changes and allow you to edit the transfer. Are you sure you want to proceed?"<br>• **And** the dialog includes "Cancel" and "Revert" buttons<br>• **When** I click "Cancel"<br>• **Then** the dialog closes and the transfer status remains "In Transit"<br>• **When** I click "Revert"<br>• **Then** the transfer status changes to "Open" and inventory is reversed<br><br>**3. Confirmation message for Received revert**<br>• **Given** I am viewing a stock transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **When** I click the "Revert to Open" button<br>• **Then** a confirmation dialog appears with the message: "Reverting this transfer to Open will reverse all inventory changes and allow you to edit the transfer. Are you sure you want to proceed?"<br>• **And** the dialog includes "Cancel" and "Revert" buttons<br>• **When** I click "Cancel"<br>• **Then** the dialog closes and the transfer status remains "Received"<br>• **When** I click "Revert"<br>• **Then** the transfer status changes to "Open" and inventory is reversed<br><br>**4. Reverting In Transit to Open restores inventory at source**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with Status = "In Transit"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location has already decreased<br>• **And** the transfer has Expected quantity at the destination location<br>• **When** I confirm reverting the transfer to Open<br>• **Then** the Status changes to "Open"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location increases by the transfer quantity (restoring the inventory)<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location remains unchanged<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date field is cleared and hidden<br>• **And** I see a success message "Stock transfer reverted to Open"<br>• **And** I can now edit all transfer fields including source, destination, items, and quantities<br><br>**5. Reverting Received to Open reverses completed transfer**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with Status = "Received"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location has decreased<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the destination location has increased<br>• **When** I confirm reverting the transfer to Open<br>• **Then** the Status changes to "Open"<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the source location increases by the transfer quantity (restoring the inventory)<br>• **And** the Committed quantity at the source location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Quantity on Hand at the destination location decreases by the transfer quantity (reversing the increase)<br>• **And** the Expected quantity at the destination location increases by the transfer quantity<br>• **And** the Available quantity recalculates at both locations as Quantity on Hand - Committed + Expected<br>• **And** the Dispatched Date and Received Date fields are cleared and hidden<br>• **And** I see a success message "Stock transfer reverted to Open"<br>• **And** I can now edit all transfer fields including source, destination, items, and quantities<br><br>**6. After reverting, transfer becomes fully editable**<br>• **Given** I have reverted a stock transfer to Open status<br>• **When** I view the transfer screen<br>• **Then** all fields are editable including: Stock Transfer #, Created Date, Reason, Source Location, Destination Location, Items table (Items, Transfer Quantity)<br>• **And** I can add or remove line items<br>• **And** I can click "Save" to keep as Open, "In Transit" to dispatch, or "Received" to complete<br>• **And** all original validation rules from FR-100 through FR-117 apply<br><br>**7. All reverts are atomic transactions**<br>• **Given** I have a stock transfer with multiple line items<br>• **And** the transfer has Status = "In Transit" or "Received"<br>• **When** I confirm reverting the transfer to Open<br>• **Then** each line item's inventory impact is reversed independently<br>• **And** all line items for the same item have their quantities summed and reversed<br>• **And** all inventory updates complete atomically | FR-104, FR-107, FR-110, FR-111, FR-112 |

